content.description: Obvious short finger crack in a shallow dihedral. The crack is followed by an easy slab scramble to the chains.
content.protection: Bring a good assortment of gear, there are plenty of options for protection. Bolted anchors equipped with rap rings up top.

content.description: Climb on good holds from one ledge to the next until you're able to reach that ear jug to clip the chains, Fun!
content.protection: 7 bolts to anchors, with two diagonal bolts with chains/ quicklinks as the anchors. Bring a 12 cm and an 18cm draw to make them equalized.
content.location: Far left bolted line, start on a corner jug in front of a tree.

content.description:
Use some side pulls/ledge holds with good feet to gain the crack then work your way to the easy roof and clip the chains.  

  If this climb was longer it would be a four star route!
content.protection:
As small as #4 BD stopper to .5 Camalot, Can be tough to find the right placement down low, but well protected through the main crack. 

  Quicklinked Anchors at the top.
content.location: Rightmost route on the wall, climbs a right facing dihedral with a small roof above.

content.description: Start on a circular cut out and go right to a good side pull. The pocket starts the sequence but where it leads to is up to the dancer to find out. A few more thought provoking moves and you'll find yourself clipping some easy chains.
content.location: The middle of the three bolted lines.

content.description: Crux down low leads to easier terrain.
content.location: This is the right-most bolted line on this wall of three sport climbs.

content.description: A left-trending corner crack system that protects well.
content.location: Continue climber's left past the bolted sport routes.

content.description: This is the furthest wall in Denny's West. Great beginner climbs on solid rock that gets sun in the late morning but would see shade later.
